{"lemma":"مُحَجَّلُو","slug":"مُحَجَّلُو","root":"ح.ج.ل","root_slug":"ح-ج-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ج-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7215"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%84%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7215","headword_ar":"مُحَجَّلٌ","root":"Hjl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wearing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHojaAl","text_ar":"اَحْجَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anklets;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adorned therewith;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to a woman [without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because men do not wear anklets]: if applied to a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shackled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 238.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,] applied to a horse, (S Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHojiylN","text_ar":"تَحْجِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as explained in the first sentence of the paragraph next preceding; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHojuwlN","text_ar":"مَحْجُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white in the place of the anklet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"wherefore the horse is thus termed: (Ham p. 53:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all four,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white; the whiteness extending"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upwards"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond the pasterns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a third,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to half,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereabout,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to two thirds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the shank."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb.) When the whiteness is in all the four legs, he is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaj~alu A^arobaEK","text_ar":"مُحَجَّلُ اَرْبَعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": when in the two hind legs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaj~alu Alr~ijolayoni","text_ar":"مُحَجَّلُ الرِّجْلَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": when in one of the hind legs, extending [upwards] beyond the pastern,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaj~alu","text_ar":"مُحَجَّلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ijoli AlyumonaY","text_ar":"الرِّجْلِ اليُمْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": when in three legs, exclusive of a hind leg or of a fore leg,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlyusoraY","text_ar":"اليُسْرَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvK muTolaqu yadK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثٍ مُطْلَقُ يَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijolK","text_ar":"رِجْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": when in the fore leg and hind leg of one side,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mumosaku AlA^ayaAmini muTolaqu","text_ar":"مُمْسَكُ الاَيَامِنِ مُطْلَقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ayaAsiri","text_ar":"الاَيَاسِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mumosaku AlA^ayaAsiri muTolaqu AlA^ayaAmini","text_ar":"مُمْسَكُ الاَيَاسِرِ مُطْلَقُ الاَيَامِنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": when on opposite sides, whether little or much,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$okuwlN","text_ar":"مَشْكُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) Hence, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~atiY Algur~u AlmuHaj~aluwna","text_ar":"اُمَّتِى الغُرُّ المُحَجَّلُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawoma AlqiyaAmapi mino A=vaAri AlwuDuwo'i","text_ar":"يَوْمَ القِيَامَةِ مِنْ ا=ثَارِ الوُضُوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My followers will be those having a whiteness on the forehead and on the wrists and ankles, on the day of resurrec tion, from the effects of the ablution for prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [Hence also, because the horse that is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaj~al","text_ar":"مَحَجَّل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is conspicuous,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba Al$~aAdixapa AlmuHaj~alapa","text_ar":"رَكِبَ الشَّادِخَةَ المُحَجَّلَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He committed a bad and notorious deed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$dx","text_ar":"شدخ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) And the saying of El-Jaadee, satirizing Leylà El-Akhyaleeyeh,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faqado rakibato A^amorFA A^agar~a muHaj~alaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For she has committed a glaring, notorious deed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Az, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN A^agar~u muHaj~alN","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ اَغَرُّ مُحَجَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day bright"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beaming with happiness and cheerfulness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 377.) ―         -b3-  Also A she-camel's udder"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a whiteness in the teats, occasioned by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiraAr","text_ar":"صِرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (K.)       -A2-  A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who keeps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleaves, to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HijaAl","text_ar":"حِجَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajalapN","text_ar":"حَجَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in like manner, a man; meaning (assumed tropical:)  one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who keeps much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habitually, to the company of women."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 238.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Mgh","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}